org.omancode.rmt.tablereader
Class AbstractTableReader

java.lang.Object
  org.omancode.rmt.tablereader.AbstractTableReader
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.lang.Iterable<java.lang.Object[]>
public abstract class AbstractTableReader
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Iterable<java.lang.Object[]>

Represents a table containing a header and cells (i.e. rows consisting of columns). Each column contains values of the same type. Column names may be specified (allowing reading of only certain columns from the table) or unspecified (in which case columns names do not need to be known in advance and all columns are loaded). Types of columns may be specified or unspecified (in which case the widest possible type is used for loading values, eg: Object or String). Missing values are supported via the use of optional cell readers, eg: CellReaders.OPTIONAL_DOUBLE.

Returns an iterator that starts at the first row after the header. Subclasses are responsible for making sure their iterator calls the column's CellReader on the values it reads.

initializeColumns

protected void initializeColumns(java.lang.String[] columnsToRead,
                                 CellReader<?>[] cellReaders)
                          throws java.io.IOException
Sets up columns. Must be called by the subclass during its construction.

Parameters:
columnsToRead - if null, all columns are read. If specified, then only these columns will be read.
cellReaders - cell readers. If null then the default Column cell reader is used for all columns.
Throws:
java.io.IOException - if problem reading header during initialisation or problem with columnsToRead or cellReaders.
